# Introduction to Pandas dataframe


csv - comma separated values 

we can make it a list of tuples to form a dataset 

df = pd.DataFrame(weather_data, columns=['day', 'temperature', 'windspeed', 'event'])

df.head() top few rows 
df.tail() bottom few rows

df[2:5] - slicing particular rows 
df.columns - gives column names 
df.____ - particular column name can be called 
df['____'] - same as accesing column
df['__', '__'] for two columns 
df['__'].max for maximum 
df['__'].min for minimum
df['___'].describe() - for all analysis related values  - different for strings 

df[df.temperature == df.temperature.max()] - to get the row of which is having max temp

df.day[df.temperature == df.temperature.max()] - to get the day 

